commit.message:
Add missing case for pretty-printer in example

The `VAR` case was missing, making it so that the example `calc.ml`
would not work on inputs such as `"x := 1; x + 1"`.

regexp library changes

1. switch from pcre to re for normal builds

2. switch from pcre to pcre2 for testing

switch from pcre to ocaml-re

also add readthedocs config-file
update to not use pcre, use ocaml-re instead
changes to make things work with older ocaml versions
add support for new let-type-constraint syntax and tests

module type for generative functors

implement shortcut syntax and a test
macos seems to have a busted "diff"; disable the test that uses diff.
